<% content_for :title do %> - SDK - Iconography<% end %>
<div id="iconography" class="widgetsdk_container">
    <h1>Iconography</h1>
    <p>This guide will help you style your widgets allowing them to fit seamlessly into the Sakai OAE suite of Widgets maintain a high standard for content presentation, and to maintain a high level of user experience across the system.</p>

    <div class="wl-widget-item first" id="iconography_styling">
        <h1 class="first">Example in-page icons</h1>
        <div class="widget-narrow-column">
            <h4>Vector icons</h4>
            <ul>
                <li><%= image_tag "accepted_icon_20x20.png", :alt => "In library/contact list" %></span>In library/contact list</li>
                <li><%= image_tag "delete_red_icon_20x20.png", :alt => "Delete/Unavailable" %>Delete/Unavailable</li>
                <li><%= image_tag "message_icon_20x20.png", :alt => "Message" %>Message</li>
                <li><%= image_tag "author_icon_26x20.png", :alt => "Author contacts", :class => "person_icon"%>Author contacts</li>
                <li><%= image_tag "share_icon_20x20.png", :alt => "Share" %>Share</li>
                <li><%= image_tag "user_icon_20x20.png", :alt => "Author details" %>Author details</li>
                <li><%= image_tag "add_icon_20x20.png", :alt => "Not saved" %>Not saved</li>
                <li><%= image_tag "delete_icon_20x20.png", :alt => "Delete (list)" %>Delete (list)</li>
            </ul>
        </div>
        <div class="widget-narrow-column">
            <h4>Vector icons (hover)</h4>
            <ul>
                <li>No hover state</li>
                <li>No hover state</li>
                <li><%= image_tag "message_hover_icon_20x20.png", :alt => "Message" %>Message</li>
                <li><%= image_tag "author_hover_icon_26x20.png", :alt => "Author contacts", :class => "person_icon" %>Author contacts</li>
                <li><%= image_tag "share_hover_icon_20x20.png", :alt => "Share" %>Share</li>
                <li><%= image_tag "user_hover_icon_20x20.png", :alt => "Author details" %>Author details</li>
                <li><%= image_tag "add_hover_icon_20x20.png", :alt => "Not saved" %>Not saved</li>
                <li><%= image_tag "delete_hover_icon_20x20.png", :alt => "Delete (list)" %>Delete (list)</li>
            </ul>
        </div>
        <div class="widget-narrow-column">
            <h4>Pixel icons</h4>
            <ul>
                <li><%= image_tag "everything_icon_20x20.png", :alt => "Everything" %>Everything</li>
                <li><%= image_tag "mycontent_icon_20x20.png", :alt => "My content" %>My content</li>
                <li><%= image_tag "shared_icon_20x20.png", :alt => "Shared with me" %>Shared with me</li>
                <li><%= image_tag "sakaidoc_icon_20x20.png", :alt => "Sakai Doc" %>Sakai Doc</li>
                <li><%= image_tag "contact_icon_20x20.png", :alt => "Small contact" %>Small contact</li>
                <li><%= image_tag "pdf_icon_20x20.png", :alt => "PDF Document" %>PDF Document</li>
            </ul>
        </div>
        <div class="widget-narrow-column">
            <h3>Usage:</h3>
            <span>Simple vector icons are used across the majority of the OAE. The exception to the rule is for the RHC small ‘Contacts’ and the ‘Add Content’ overlay where the style is of a ‘pixel’ base</span>
        </div>
        <hr class="wl-push wl-hidden"/>

        <h1>Default list icons</h1>
        <div class="widget-narrow-column">
            <h4>Memberships</h4>
            <div class="widget-narrow-column-subcolumn">
                <%= image_tag "memberships_icon_50x50.png", :alt => "Memberships Large Icon", :class => "large" %>
                <span>50 x 50 px</span>
            </div>
            <div class="widget-narrow-column-subcolumn">
                <%= image_tag "memberships_icon_35x35.png", :alt => "Memberships small Icon", :class => "small" %>
                <span>35 x 35 px</span>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="widget-narrow-column">
            <h4>User</h4>
            <div class="widget-narrow-column-subcolumn">
                <%= image_tag "user_icon_50x50.png", :alt => "Memberships Large Icon", :class => "large" %>
                <span>50 x 50 px</span>
            </div>
            <div class="widget-narrow-column-subcolumn">
                <%= image_tag "user_icon_35x35.png", :alt => "Memberships small Icon", :class => "small" %>
                <span>35 x 35 px</span>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="widget-narrow-column">
            <h4>World</h4>
            <div class="widget-narrow-column-subcolumn">
                <%= image_tag "world_icon_50x50.png", :alt => "Memberships Large Icon", :class => "large" %>
                <span>50 x 50 px</span>
            </div>
            <div class="widget-narrow-column-subcolumn">
                <%= image_tag "world_icon_35x35.png", :alt => "Memberships small Icon", :class => "small" %>
                <span>35 x 35 px</span>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="widget-narrow-column">
            <h3>Usage:</h3>
            <span>These appear by default if a user hasn’t uploaded an image for them selves or one can’t be extracted from a piece of content.</span>
        </div>
        <hr class="wl-push wl-hidden">

        <h1>Widget store icons</h1>
        <div class="widget-narrow-column">
            <h4>Detail icon</h4>
            <%= image_tag "widgetstore_icon_100x100.png", :alt => "Widget store large icon" %>
            <span>100 x 100 px</span>
        </div>
        <div class="widget-narrow-column">
            <h3>Browse icon</h3>
            <%= image_tag "widgetstore_icon_50x50.png", :alt => "Widget store small icon" %>
            <span>50 x 50 px</span>
        </div>
        <div class="widget-narrow-column">&nbsp;</div>
        <div class="widget-narrow-column">
            <h3>Usage:</h3>
            <span>To be used as an icon for your designed widget. If you can’t design one yourself and have already had your widget approved for te OAE we may be able to help.</span>
            <%= link_to "Send us a message", "/sdk/help", :class => "wl-regular-link"%>
        </div>
        <hr class="wl-push wl-hidden">

        <h1>Header button icons</h1>
        <div id="iconography_container">
            <button type="button" class="wl-button wl-header-button">Message<div class="wl-icon wl-message-icon"></div></button>
            <button type="button" class="wl-button wl-header-button">Request connection<div class="wl-icon wl-requestconnection-icon"></div></button>
            <button type="button" class="wl-button wl-header-button wl-nopadding-button"><div class="wl-icon wl-cogwheel-icon"></div>&#9660;</button>
            <button type="button" class="wl-button wl-header-button">Share<div class="wl-icon wl-share-icon"></div></button>
            <button type="button" class="wl-button wl-header-button">Save<div class="wl-icon wl-saved-icon"></div></button>
            <button type="button" class="wl-button wl-header-button">Connection request sent<div class="wl-icon wl-connectionrequestsent-icon"></div></button>
            <button type="button" class="wl-button wl-header-button">Accept invitation to connect<div class="wl-icon wl-acceptconnectionrequest-icon"></div></button>
            <div class="wl-connected-label">
                <%= image_tag "accepted_icon_20x20.png", :alt => "Connected" %>
                Connected
            </div>
            <button type="button" class="wl-button wl-header-button">Download<div class="wl-icon wl-download-icon"></div></button>
            <button type="button" class="wl-button wl-header-button">Save<div class="wl-icon wl-save-icon"></div></button>
            <div class="s3d-regular-links" id="iconography_entity_details">
                <span class="first">
                    <%= image_tag "usedby_icon_15x10.png", :alt => "Used By Icon" %>
                    Used by
                    <button type="button" class="wl-link-button">2053 people</button>, and <button type="button" class="wl-link-button">4 places</button>
                </span>
                <span>
                    <%= image_tag "comment_icon_15x10.png", :alt => "Comments Icon" %> <button type="button" class="wl-link-button">256 Comments</button>
                </span>
                <span>
                    <%= image_tag "chain_icon_15x10.png", :alt => "Chain Icon" %>
                    Visible to anyone with the link
                </span>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>